[Auction "E"]
1NT 2H 3H pass 4C pass 5C pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "1b9d9e2c2c37b0a61a945619765308a8a4d089548b0fa748538740d7c16ebaac"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/lebensohl"]
[Student "S"]
{Partner's bid asks if you have 4 \Ss, and denies a \H stopper. (DIRECT DENIES)

You don't have 4 \Ss, nor can you stop \Hs. You have no choice but to bid one of the 4-card Minor suits, so you go up-the-line and bid 4\C. Partner bids 5\C.}

